Text.SourceString: Yesterday...unforgettable. You looked...beyond my dreams, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Yesterday...unforgettable. You looked...beyond my dreams, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I'm one lucky bloke.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm one lucky bloke.

Text.SourceString: Got breakfast ready.//Important you start your day right, baby. Eat up.
Text.LocalizedString: Got breakfast ready.//Important you start your day right, baby. Eat up.

Text.SourceString: Here, cutie-pie...this is for you.
Text.LocalizedString: Here, cutie-pie...this is for you.

Text.SourceString: So, I'm officially off the market.
Text.LocalizedString: So, I'm officially off the market.

Text.SourceString: Come here, you...cutie-pie.
Text.LocalizedString: Come here, you...cutie-pie.

Text.SourceString: Our farm's a fair bit closer to the B.O.S. guild than <NpcName>Anne</>'s.//<portrait=normal>It's a timesaver.
Text.LocalizedString: Our farm's a fair bit closer to the B.O.S. guild than <NpcName>Anne</>'s.//<portrait=normal>It's a timesaver.

Text.SourceString: I've always had a bit of a dream about living on a farm...or in some big open space.
Text.LocalizedString: I've always had a bit of a dream about living on a farm...or in some big open space.

Text.SourceString: Never really saw the why of it before, so never went for it.
Text.LocalizedString: Never really saw the why of it before, so never went for it.

Text.SourceString: Don't feel the need to go walkabout...quite comfy here.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't feel the need to go walkabout...quite comfy here.

Text.SourceString: How about we keep things low key today, cutie-pie?
Text.LocalizedString: How about we keep things low key today, cutie-pie?

Text.SourceString: My aim isn't great lately, reckon I need to up my training game.
Text.LocalizedString: My aim isn't great lately, reckon I need to up my training game.

Text.SourceString: Got plans to pop over to <NpcName>Jio Dan</>'s place today, see what they're getting up to.
Text.LocalizedString: Got plans to pop over to <NpcName>Jio Dan</>'s place today, see what they're getting up to.

Text.SourceString: Don't let me forget to pen a note to Mom tomorrow, cutie-pie.//Nah, today just won't do.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't let me forget to pen a note to Mom tomorrow, cutie-pie.//Nah, today just won't do.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Anne</>'s been threatening about coming here and bunking with us if I don't.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Anne</>'s been threatening about coming here and bunking with us if I don't.

Text.SourceString: Sent over some cookies to Mom, thought she might appreciate some holiday treats.
Text.LocalizedString: Sent over some cookies to Mom, thought she might appreciate some holiday treats.

Text.SourceString: Need to sort something for lil' <NpcName>Zoe</> too, reckon I'll get onto that tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Need to sort something for lil' <NpcName>Zoe</> too, reckon I'll get onto that tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Might pop by the shelter later, gotta do a tally on the pet food.
Text.LocalizedString: Might pop by the shelter later, gotta do a tally on the pet food.

Text.SourceString: I'll see if <NpcName>Raj</>'s got some time today to lend a hand.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll see if <NpcName>Raj</>'s got some time today to lend a hand.

Text.SourceString: I like watching you from here, you look good handling farm chores.
Text.LocalizedString: I like watching you from here, you look good handling farm chores.

Text.SourceString: Need a hand there, cutie?
Text.LocalizedString: Need a hand there, cutie?

Text.SourceString: Took a walk this morning, nothing tops the sunrise from our farm.
Text.LocalizedString: Took a walk this morning, nothing tops the sunrise from our farm.

Text.SourceString: I've now scheduled to write to Mom every fortnight in my calendar.//It feels good.
Text.LocalizedString: I've now scheduled to write to Mom every fortnight in my calendar.//It feels good.

Text.SourceString: Still, you'd think that'd get <NpcName>Anne</> to stop hassling me, but nope.
Text.LocalizedString: Still, you'd think that'd get <NpcName>Anne</> to stop hassling me, but nope.

Text.SourceString: Might drop by to see my sis today, baby.
Text.LocalizedString: Might drop by to see my sis today, baby.

Text.SourceString: But, nah, there's a bit of snow coming down.//Can't be bothered to trudge through the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: But, nah, there's a bit of snow coming down.//Can't be bothered to trudge through the snow.

Text.SourceString: Always smells a bit like hummus around here, doesn't it? Not that I'm whinging.
Text.LocalizedString: Always smells a bit like hummus around here, doesn't it? Not that I'm whinging.

Text.SourceString: What brings you to this neck of the woods, cutie?//<portrait=normal>Off to the cavern?
Text.LocalizedString: What brings you to this neck of the woods, cutie?//<portrait=normal>Off to the cavern?

Text.SourceString: Weather like this...it's best enjoyed right here, don't ya think?
Text.LocalizedString: Weather like this...it's best enjoyed right here, don't ya think?

Text.SourceString: Looks like the cavern is well managed.//<portrait=happy>We did well, didn't we, cutie?
Text.LocalizedString: Looks like the cavern is well managed.//<portrait=happy>We did well, didn't we, cutie?

Text.SourceString: There's plenty of shade around here.
Text.LocalizedString: There's plenty of shade around here.

Text.SourceString: I'll be back in time for dinner, don't you worry, cutie-pie.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll be back in time for dinner, don't you worry, cutie-pie.

Text.SourceString: With me, you've got nothing to worry about.//I want you to feel safe.
Text.LocalizedString: With me, you've got nothing to worry about.//I want you to feel safe.

Text.SourceString: Thought I'd grab some hot cocoa before heading off to work.
Text.LocalizedString: Thought I'd grab some hot cocoa before heading off to work.

Text.SourceString: Had brekkie at home, but I'm feeling a bit hungry again.
Text.LocalizedString: Had brekkie at home, but I'm feeling a bit hungry again.

Text.SourceString: Almost finished up here, cutie.//<portrait=annoyed>Just got to log the final inventory after this.
Text.LocalizedString: Almost finished up here, cutie.//<portrait=annoyed>Just got to log the final inventory after this.

Text.SourceString: The mayor came by and checked on us earlier, all smooth sailing.
Text.LocalizedString: The mayor came by and checked on us earlier, all smooth sailing.

Text.SourceString: There's a charm about you, baby, that's really hard to find.
Text.LocalizedString: There's a charm about you, baby, that's really hard to find.

Text.SourceString: When you smile, it's like everything just gets a little better.
Text.LocalizedString: When you smile, it's like everything just gets a little better.

Text.SourceString: Whoa, where are you headed, cutie? You look...stunning.
Text.LocalizedString: Whoa, where are you headed, cutie? You look...stunning.

Text.SourceString: How did I... I'm so lucky.
Text.LocalizedString: How did I... I'm so lucky.

Text.SourceString: Come closer, let me give you a kiss.
Text.LocalizedString: Come closer, let me give you a kiss.

Text.SourceString: Lots of people here, like us, grow their own food.//There’s a small garden in front of the guild too… It’s <NpcName>Kira</>'s.
Text.LocalizedString: Lots of people here, like us, grow their own food.//There’s a small garden in front of the guild too… It’s <NpcName>Kira</>'s.

Text.SourceString: I’d set all the animals at the shelter free if I could. But it wouldn’t be safe for them.//They don’t know how to live in the wild.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d set all the animals at the shelter free if I could. But it wouldn’t be safe for them.//They don’t know how to live in the wild.

Text.SourceString: I don’t go to the cavern.//I don’t have any reason to since I don’t mine or collect artifacts.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t go to the cavern.//I don’t have any reason to since I don’t mine or collect artifacts.

Text.SourceString: Can you believe this heat? I’ve never sweat so much in my life.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you believe this heat? I’ve never sweat so much in my life.

Text.SourceString: People here seem to like Spring weather.//They’re so annoyingly vocal about it.
Text.LocalizedString: People here seem to like Spring weather.//They’re so annoyingly vocal about it.

Text.SourceString: I could use some homemade tomato soup.
Text.LocalizedString: I could use some homemade tomato soup.

Text.SourceString: The birds are back.//It’s nice to walk outside with them around again.
Text.LocalizedString: The birds are back.//It’s nice to walk outside with them around again.

Text.SourceString: This? Hot?//<portrait=normal>Maybe it’s a bit hot, but nothing unbearable.
Text.LocalizedString: This? Hot?//<portrait=normal>Maybe it’s a bit hot, but nothing unbearable.

Text.SourceString: Breathe that Winter air in, my Garden Rake.//It’ll toughen you up.
Text.LocalizedString: Breathe that Winter air in, my Garden Rake.//It’ll toughen you up.

Text.SourceString: Caught someone slipping in the rain the other day…wearing sandals. Tch.//And he wondered why he slipped.
Text.LocalizedString: Caught someone slipping in the rain the other day…wearing sandals. Tch.//And he wondered why he slipped.

Text.SourceString: You need a pair of nice sturdy boots for walking in the rain.//My boots have saved me from slipping many times.
Text.LocalizedString: You need a pair of nice sturdy boots for walking in the rain.//My boots have saved me from slipping many times.

Text.SourceString: Fishing isn’t my thing. I could if I had to, of course.//What is it? Are you in the mood to have fish for dinner? I'll go get some if you want.
Text.LocalizedString: Fishing isn’t my thing. I could if I had to, of course.//What is it? Are you in the mood to have fish for dinner? I'll go get some if you want.

Text.SourceString: The hot spring is free. I wonder why more people don’t go there.
Text.LocalizedString: The hot spring is free. I wonder why more people don’t go there.

Text.SourceString: It’s safe here in Fall. It isn’t too hot.//In some places, this is wildfire season.//I’ve run away from several of those myself.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s safe here in Fall. It isn’t too hot.//In some places, this is wildfire season.//I’ve run away from several of those myself.

Text.SourceString: Favorite season? I don’t have one.//All seasons are the same to me.
Text.LocalizedString: Favorite season? I don’t have one.//All seasons are the same to me.

Text.SourceString: Favorite worm? Is this a trick question? Should I say it's you?//<portrait=happy>Well, you're my favorite in everything, baby. Favorite season, favorite worm, favorite whatever...
Text.LocalizedString: Favorite worm? Is this a trick question? Should I say it's you?//<portrait=happy>Well, you're my favorite in everything, baby. Favorite season, favorite worm, favorite whatever...

Text.SourceString: Why are you out here in the rain?//What’s so important, baby? Let's get you inside. I don't want you running around in the rain like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Why are you out here in the rain?//What’s so important, baby? Let's get you inside. I don't want you running around in the rain like this.

Text.SourceString: Why are you out here in the storm?//What’s so important, baby? Let's get you inside. I don't want you running around in the rain like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Why are you out here in the storm?//What’s so important, baby? Let's get you inside. I don't want you running around in the rain like this.

Text.SourceString: Watch out if you’re headed into the cavern today. <Italic>They</> seem agitated.
Text.LocalizedString: Watch out if you’re headed into the cavern today. <Italic>They</> seem agitated.

Text.SourceString: Would you like me to accompany you?
Text.LocalizedString: Would you like me to accompany you?

Text.SourceString: Your hair is wet.
Text.LocalizedString: Your hair is wet.

Text.SourceString: Your hair is wet.
Text.LocalizedString: Your hair is wet.

Text.SourceString: My scar might look scary to people, but I’m not too worried about it.//My face is fine. Still functioning as intended.
Text.LocalizedString: My scar might look scary to people, but I’m not too worried about it.//My face is fine. Still functioning as intended.

Text.SourceString: Poor Chap, the cat that scratched me, didn’t mean it.// I was about to give him his vaccine, and he was scared. But he was very brave about it at the end of the day.
Text.LocalizedString: Poor Chap, the cat that scratched me, didn’t mean it.// I was about to give him his vaccine, and he was scared. But he was very brave about it at the end of the day.

Text.SourceString: I love the cold. Mmm…invigorating!
Text.LocalizedString: I love the cold. Mmm…invigorating!

Text.SourceString: Saw Funbucket on my way here.
Text.LocalizedString: Saw Funbucket on my way here.

Text.SourceString: We should get you a tin hat, baby. I bet you'd look adorable in it!
Text.LocalizedString: We should get you a tin hat, baby. I bet you'd look adorable in it!

Text.SourceString: It’s quiet tonight, just how I like it.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s quiet tonight, just how I like it.

Text.SourceString: It’s quiet tonight. A little too quiet.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s quiet tonight. A little too quiet.

Text.SourceString: I’m visiting <NPCName>Rafael</> later today.//My sword could use some sharpening.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m visiting <NPCName>Rafael</> later today.//My sword could use some sharpening.

Text.SourceString: Gah, it’s Winter. Means he’s busy upgrading farming tools.//<portrait=normal>I’ll wait till Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: Gah, it’s Winter. Means he’s busy upgrading farming tools.//<portrait=normal>I’ll wait till Spring.

Text.SourceString: My favorite thing to get from the Coffee Corner is hot cocoa.//Not a fan of coffee. It’s a tad bitter for my taste.
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite thing to get from the Coffee Corner is hot cocoa.//Not a fan of coffee. It’s a tad bitter for my taste.

Text.SourceString: I’m sick of hearing people whine about how they can’t handle a little bit of cold weather.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m sick of hearing people whine about how they can’t handle a little bit of cold weather.

Text.SourceString: This job at the animal shelter doesn’t pay much.
Text.LocalizedString: This job at the animal shelter doesn’t pay much.

Text.SourceString: Good thing making a lot of money doesn’t interest me.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing making a lot of money doesn’t interest me.

Text.SourceString: I’m here to take care of the shelter.//Wanna help out, cutie-pie?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m here to take care of the shelter.//Wanna help out, cutie-pie?

Text.SourceString: Gotta make sure the shelter is clean and safe for the animals.//They don’t have anywhere else to go.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta make sure the shelter is clean and safe for the animals.//They don’t have anywhere else to go.

Text.SourceString: Some of the animals at the shelter just wandered here from Hillside or the forest. Like Taco, the vineyard’s dog.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the animals at the shelter just wandered here from Hillside or the forest. Like Taco, the vineyard’s dog.

Text.SourceString: I need to clean all the litter boxes today.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to clean all the litter boxes today.

Text.SourceString: It gets busy in here on the weekend.//There’s a yoga class on Saturdays.
Text.LocalizedString: It gets busy in here on the weekend.//There’s a yoga class on Saturdays.

Text.SourceString: Me? No, thanks. I don’t think I’ll be joining the yoga class anytime soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Me? No, thanks. I don’t think I’ll be joining the yoga class anytime soon.

Text.SourceString: Summer’s almost here.//Might need to change up my gear.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer’s almost here.//Might need to change up my gear.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice and hot today.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice and hot today.

Text.SourceString: I like reading books at the beach. Join me?
Text.LocalizedString: I like reading books at the beach. Join me?

Text.SourceString: How about I grab some drinks from the shack for you, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Sound good?
Text.LocalizedString: How about I grab some drinks from the shack for you, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Sound good?

Text.SourceString: Hot spring is empty this time of year.//Perfect.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot spring is empty this time of year.//Perfect.

Text.SourceString: Weird that shiitake only grow here in Spring.//They grow in Spring and Fall in Beluga.
Text.LocalizedString: Weird that shiitake only grow here in Spring.//They grow in Spring and Fall in Beluga.

Text.SourceString: The sunscreen they sell around here comes in tiny little bottles.//It barely covers my legs. Tch.//<portrait=angry>What a scam!
Text.LocalizedString: The sunscreen they sell around here comes in tiny little bottles.//It barely covers my legs. Tch.//<portrait=angry>What a scam!

Text.SourceString: Here I thought I was gonna read my book in peace. Tch. Seagulls everywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: Here I thought I was gonna read my book in peace. Tch. Seagulls everywhere.

Text.SourceString: This book is from the library.
Text.LocalizedString: This book is from the library.

Text.SourceString: I don’t buy books. I prefer to read the free ones.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t buy books. I prefer to read the free ones.

Text.SourceString: I’m feeling a little sore from training the other day.//<portrait=sad>At least now I’m relaxing here on the beach, but it doesn’t seem to help my muscle recovery.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m feeling a little sore from training the other day.//<portrait=sad>At least now I’m relaxing here on the beach, but it doesn’t seem to help my muscle recovery.

Text.SourceString: I might need to hit the hot spring on the way home. Just a dip or something.//<portrait=sad>Can you give me a massage later?
Text.LocalizedString: I might need to hit the hot spring on the way home. Just a dip or something.//<portrait=sad>Can you give me a massage later?

Text.SourceString: Shiitake are great. Other mushrooms are okay.//Not that good.
Text.LocalizedString: Shiitake are great. Other mushrooms are okay.//Not that good.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna be here for a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna be here for a bit.

Text.SourceString: Didn’t bring anything to eat today. I thought I could just pop by the shack if I get hungry.//<portrait=annoyed>I did get some coffee this morning. Bad decision. Should’ve gotten the hot cocoa instead.
Text.LocalizedString: Didn’t bring anything to eat today. I thought I could just pop by the shack if I get hungry.//<portrait=annoyed>I did get some coffee this morning. Bad decision. Should’ve gotten the hot cocoa instead.

Text.SourceString: Are we heading home together or you got something else lined up after this?
Text.LocalizedString: Are we heading home together or you got something else lined up after this?

Text.SourceString: The hot water feels good.
Text.LocalizedString: The hot water feels good.

Text.SourceString: I can feel my muscles relaxing.
Text.LocalizedString: I can feel my muscles relaxing.

Text.SourceString: I'm enjoying our time here.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm enjoying our time here.

Text.SourceString: Give my back a scrub, baby?
Text.LocalizedString: Give my back a scrub, baby?

Text.SourceString: Could I steal a kiss now or should we save it for home? I mean...
Text.LocalizedString: Could I steal a kiss now or should we save it for home? I mean...

Text.SourceString: I’m liking this part of the forest way more than the woodland.//<portrait=angry>There are more bugs here, though. Annoying.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m liking this part of the forest way more than the woodland.//<portrait=angry>There are more bugs here, though. Annoying.

Text.SourceString: Training day for me today.
Text.LocalizedString: Training day for me today.

Text.SourceString: Watch your step.
Text.LocalizedString: Watch your step.

Text.SourceString: Nice day, huh?//I like the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: Nice day, huh?//I like the rain.

Text.SourceString: Nice day, huh?//I like the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: Nice day, huh?//I like the snow.

Text.SourceString: Be careful out there.
Text.LocalizedString: Be careful out there.

Text.SourceString: Be careful out there. It’s icy.
Text.LocalizedString: Be careful out there. It’s icy.

Text.SourceString: You look pretty good when you’re all covered in dirt from working on the farm. It suits you.
Text.LocalizedString: You look pretty good when you’re all covered in dirt from working on the farm. It suits you.

Text.SourceString: If we ever get tired of our usual roles, maybe I could take care of the animals, and you could…take care of me?
Text.LocalizedString: If we ever get tired of our usual roles, maybe I could take care of the animals, and you could…take care of me?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Paul’s</> a good guy.//Dude’s solid. I like him.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Paul’s</> a good guy.//Dude’s solid. I like him.

Text.SourceString: He could tackle a bear if he wanted to. He can protect my niece fine.
Text.LocalizedString: He could tackle a bear if he wanted to. He can protect my niece fine.

Text.SourceString: This is a nice spot.
Text.LocalizedString: This is a nice spot.

Text.SourceString: Hot peppers? Why would anyone willingly set their mouth on fire? No, thank you.//Not a chance.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot peppers? Why would anyone willingly set their mouth on fire? No, thank you.//Not a chance.

Text.SourceString: Goat cheese – the bane of my existence.//Can’t fathom how anyone can eat that stuff without gagging.
Text.LocalizedString: Goat cheese – the bane of my existence.//Can’t fathom how anyone can eat that stuff without gagging.

Text.SourceString: Shiitake’s in season, right? Good stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Shiitake’s in season, right? Good stuff.

Text.SourceString: Snow’s beautiful…like you.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow’s beautiful…like you.

Text.SourceString: The animals in the shelter need extra care in this cold weather.
Text.LocalizedString: The animals in the shelter need extra care in this cold weather.

Text.SourceString: The scarf? It’s <NpcName>Anne</>'s. Why? Does it look weird? It’s warm.
Text.LocalizedString: The scarf? It’s <NpcName>Anne</>'s. Why? Does it look weird? It’s warm.

Text.SourceString: I don’t wanna spend money on new scarves. It’s wasteful.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wanna spend money on new scarves. It’s wasteful.

Text.SourceString: It’s harvest time, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Better make the most of it.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s harvest time, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Better make the most of it.

Text.SourceString: The animals in the shelter need extra water in this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: The animals in the shelter need extra water in this weather.

Text.SourceString: It could be 100 degrees out, but I’m never wearing sandals. I don’t care.//Gotta protect my feet.
Text.LocalizedString: It could be 100 degrees out, but I’m never wearing sandals. I don’t care.//Gotta protect my feet.

Text.SourceString: Boots are the way to go – sturdy and reliable.
Text.LocalizedString: Boots are the way to go – sturdy and reliable.

Text.SourceString: I always found comfort in the company of animals.//<portrait=happy>They don’t judge, they don’t ask questions. They just are.
Text.LocalizedString: I always found comfort in the company of animals.//<portrait=happy>They don’t judge, they don’t ask questions. They just are.

Text.SourceString: Don’t get me wrong, art’s great and all, if you’re into that kind of thing.//I should stick to what I know.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t get me wrong, art’s great and all, if you’re into that kind of thing.//I should stick to what I know.

Text.SourceString: I prefer simple, hearty meals like tomato soup, smoked salmon, hot cocoa… Does that count?
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer simple, hearty meals like tomato soup, smoked salmon, hot cocoa… Does that count?

Text.SourceString: Anyway, things that don’t require a lot of fuss.//Life’s complicated enough as it is.
Text.LocalizedString: Anyway, things that don’t require a lot of fuss.//Life’s complicated enough as it is.

Text.SourceString: I’m terrible at picking out gifts.//I never know what to get people.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m terrible at picking out gifts.//I never know what to get people.

Text.SourceString: Music’s not really my thing, but I can appreciate a good beat when I hear one.
Text.LocalizedString: Music’s not really my thing, but I can appreciate a good beat when I hear one.

Text.SourceString: Taking care of animals can be messy work.//You gotta be prepared to get scratched and all.
Text.LocalizedString: Taking care of animals can be messy work.//You gotta be prepared to get scratched and all.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind it one bit. It’s part of the job.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind it one bit. It’s part of the job.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I’ll help my sister and <NpcName>Paul</> with their wildlife shoots.//<portrait=normal>It’s pretty cool getting up close and personal with some of these animals.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I’ll help my sister and <NpcName>Paul</> with their wildlife shoots.//<portrait=normal>It’s pretty cool getting up close and personal with some of these animals.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Anne</> and I used to spend hours in the forest behind our house, watching the wildlife.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Anne</> and I used to spend hours in the forest behind our house, watching the wildlife.

Text.SourceString: We’d track animals, build forts, and just explore.
Text.LocalizedString: We’d track animals, build forts, and just explore.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Zoe</> got me a husky calendar for my birthday a few years ago. Told her I liked it… And now she gets me the same one every year.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Zoe</> got me a husky calendar for my birthday a few years ago. Told her I liked it… And now she gets me the same one every year.

Text.SourceString: But you know what? I like it every single time.
Text.LocalizedString: But you know what? I like it every single time.

Text.SourceString: The wind is nice today.
Text.LocalizedString: The wind is nice today.
